# Docs — Single Canon

**Entry point:** [docs/README.md](../../docs/README.md)  
**Agent entry:** [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)  
**Inventory:** [docs/DOCUMENTATION_INVENTORY.md](../../docs/DOCUMENTATION_INVENTORY.md)

This file is the **only** place that defines how agents and humans change documentation. Product/runtime rules stay in their canons and other `.cursor/rules/*`.

## Find before write

Before creating **any** new file under `docs/`:

1. Read [docs/README.md](../../docs/README.md) — which of the five entry sections owns the topic?
2. Search `docs/**/*.md` for the topic keywords.
3. Check [docs/DOCUMENTATION_INVENTORY.md](../../docs/DOCUMENTATION_INVENTORY.md).

If a document already covers the topic → **update that document**. Do not add `_V2`, parallel maps, or a second SoT.

## One entry point

All living docs are reached **only** through the five sections in `docs/README.md`:

1. Product Map  
2. Technical Architecture  
3. Generation Registry  
4. Implementation Status  
5. Screen Maps  

Do not advertise a separate “main product SoT” outside that index. Until consolidated files exist (PR-2+), README points at the **interim** authorities listed there.

## Soft gate for new MAP / REGISTRY / PASSPORT / CANON

New files whose names suggest a parallel authority (`*MAP*`, `*REGISTRY*`, `*PASSPORT*`, `*CANON*`, dated compliance audits that restate architecture) are **discouraged**, not auto-blocked.

Allowed **only when** an existing document in the right section **cannot** be extended without becoming unreadable or mixing unrelated concerns.

In that case the PR description **must** state:

1. Which existing document was considered  
2. Why it could not be updated  
3. Which README section owns the new file  
4. That [DOCUMENTATION_INVENTORY.md](../../docs/DOCUMENTATION_INVENTORY.md) was updated in the same PR  

Audits may record **gaps and links** to canon. They must not become a second architecture narrative.

## Code before docs

1. Prefer reading and changing **code / API / prompts in repo**.  
2. Update the existing canon to match reality.  
3. Do not invent target architecture docs for unwired systems.

## Inventory before delete

Do not archive or delete docs until the inventory row is reviewed: unique decisions must be merged into an entry-section document first.

## Anti-patterns

```text
❌ New "product SoT" beside docs/README.md
❌ Block passport / pipeline map / prompt registry that duplicates an existing registry or reconstruction doc
❌ Audit that redefines architecture instead of listing deltas
❌ Docs-only PR that adds principles without a code or contract change
```

```text
✅ Extend TODAYFLOW_PRODUCT_MODEL / screen canon / prompt registry in place
✅ Point README section at one interim authority
✅ Inventory row updated when docs are added or retired
✅ PR explains why a rare new MAP/REGISTRY/PASSPORT/CANON was unavoidable
```
